[5] India (Madhya Pradesh state)
Date: Sun 15 Nov 2015
Source: WebIndia123 [edited]
http://news.webindia123.com/news/Articles/India/20151115/2725431.html


WHO to examine suspected measles patients in Guna
-------------------------------------------------
A World Health Organisation (WHO) team will examine suspected measles patients in 2 villages -- Chhoti Kanthi and Badi Kanthi -- of Madhya Pradesh's Guna district where 11 children were found to be suffering from the disease 5 days back. Disease Monitoring Committee's District Incharge Satyendra Singh Raghuvanshi said that 7 children in Chhoti Kanthi village and 4 in Badi Kanthi village have been detected to be suffering from measles. All the children are aged between 2-12 years. A report has been sent to the states Health Directorate. Samples would be collected in the presence of WHO officials and sent for examination. On the reports arrival, the Health Department would chalk out strategy for vaccination. Chief Medical and Health Officer Sarojini Jevek said that all the children are stable, The WHO collects sample when more than 5 cases come up so that measures could be taken to contain the disease from spreading. Presently, all the cases have been classified under suspected category and would be confirmed only after examination.

